Three men suspected of committing several crimes have been stoned to death in Tshandama outside Thohoyandou in Limpopo. The police’s Motlafela Mojapelo says two of the deceased have been identified as 34-year-old Meshack Munyai and 30-year-old Azwindini Mudau from Tshakhuma village. He says the third man has not been identified. Mojapelo says police have launched a manhunt for the suspects who killed the three men. Mojapelo says: “The provincial commissioner of SAPS in Limpopo General Nneke Ledwaba has strongly condemned the action of the community members and has ordered police to hunt down the killers and bring them to book.”